# Reference accessed: 2026-05-31 via gh api.
#
# dw_gdb CLI surface (decoded from opts array +
# GetLongOpts call):
#   -S <sp> / -s <sp> / --serialport=<sp>
#                         serial port path (e.g. /dev/ttyUSB0 or COM3)
#   -B <bd> / -b <bd> / --baud=<bd>
#                         baud rate (auto-scan if omitted)
#   -T <tp> / -t <tp> / --tcpport=<tp>
#                         TCP port for GDB remote (default: 1234)
#   -I / -i / --ispenable
#                         temporarily disable DWEN fuse (enables ISP)
#   -V / -v / --verbose   enable verbose debug output
#   -H / -h / -? / --help display help and exit
#
# dw_gdb is a debugWIRE-to-GDB bridge — provides
# a GDB-RSP (Remote Serial Protocol) server over
# TCP that translates GDB commands into AVR
# microcontroller debugWIRE protocol messages,
# allowing GDB to debug AVR chips via their
# single-wire DWLINK protocol.  Authored by
# ccrause.  6 GH stars (specialized embedded-
# systems tool).  Sister tools: avr-gdb (GDB
# variant for AVR; in corpus), dwdebug
# (alternative debugWIRE client), avrdude (AVR
# downloader/uploader; in corpus), avr-gcc (in
# corpus).
